Before Me, the undersigned Notary Public, personally came and appeared Michael Mann, the duly authorized agent of
Lakeside Project Solutions for the purposes of only signing and presenting for filing this Claim of Lien, who was duly
swom and says that, pursuant to the information provided by Lakeside Project Solutions the information on this Claim of
Lien is accurate and true. And, solely as represented by Lakeside Project Solutions through information provided, that in
accordance with a contract with the Hiring Party, the Lienor Furnished the labor, services, and/or materials above-
identified as the Services, said Services were furnished on the above-described Property.
The Property is owned by the Property Owner.
As represented by Lakeside Project Solutions the total contract price between the Hiring Party and the Lienor is above-
identified as the Amount of Total Contract. Of this amount, the above-identified Amount of Total Claim remains unpaid, the
Services were first furnished to the Property on the above-identified Dates Services First Furnished, and last furnished to
the Property on the above-identified Dates Services Last Furnished, and the Lienor delivered the required preliminary
Notice to Owner on the above-indicated dates to the above-indicated parties, if any.
Signed:
Lakeside Project Solutions, Lienor
Signed by: Michael Mann agent
Date: May 18, 2022
Sworn to (or affirmed) and subscribed before me, Notary Public, on May 18, 2022
